---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'July 16, 2026';
const COMPANY = 'Anton Liberant';
const EMAIL = 'anliberant@gmail.com';
const COUNTRY = 'Israel';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy - AI Karma Tracker" description="How AI Karma Tracker handles your data.">
  <main class="wrap legal" style="max-width:760px; padding:56px 24px 20px">
    <h1 style="font-size:38px">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:8px">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>AI Karma Tracker (“we”, “us”) is a browser extension and website that helps you track AI usage limits. We keep data handling minimal on purpose: the extension is built to run on your own machine.</p>

    <h2>The extension runs locally</h2>
    <p>The extension reads the usage limits of AI tools you are <b>already logged into</b> (Claude, ChatGPT, Codex, Cursor, Grok, Perplexity) using your browser’s existing session. Those reads happen in your browser, against those providers’ own endpoints. Your usage data is stored <b>locally</b> in your browser (<code>chrome.storage</code>) and is <b>not transmitted to us</b>. We do not collect your passwords, cookies, browsing history, or the contents of your AI conversations.</p>

    <h2>Data that leaves your device</h2>
    <p><b>License verification.</b> When you activate Pro, the extension sends the <b>license key you paste</b> to Gumroad to verify it’s valid. We do not receive or store your card details.</p>
    <p><b>Telegram alerts (optional).</b> If you choose to connect Telegram, we store a random link code and your <b>Telegram chat ID</b> on our relay so it can deliver alerts to you. Nothing else is sent. You can disconnect at any time from the extension settings, which removes the link.</p>

    <h2>What we do not do</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or transfer your data. We do not run advertising trackers. We do not track the web pages you visit or log your activity.</p>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>We rely on: <b>Gumroad</b> (payments, tax and license verification, as Merchant of Record), <b>Supabase</b> (serverless functions that power the optional Telegram alert relay), <b>Telegram</b> (only if you enable alerts), and the <b>Chrome Web Store</b> (distribution). Each processes data under its own policy.</p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>Telegram links are kept until you disconnect. Gumroad retains purchase and license records per its own policy. You can request deletion of any data we hold by emailing us.</p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the personal data we hold about you. Contact <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a> and we will respond within a reasonable time.</p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>AI Karma Tracker is not directed to children under 16 and we do not knowingly collect their data.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy; material changes will be reflected by the “last updated” date above.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>{COMPANY}, {COUNTRY}. Questions: <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a>.</p>
  </main>
  <style>
    .legal h2 { font-size:22px; margin:28px 0 6px; }
    .legal p { margin:10px 0; color:#334155; line-height:1.75; }
    .legal code { background:var(--bg-soft); padding:2px 6px; border-radius:6px; font-size:14px; }
    .legal a { color:var(--brand); font-weight:600; }
  </style>
</Base>
